WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:02.570
male announcer:
IN THE CRIMINAL JUSTICE SYSTEM,

00:02.603 --> 00:04.038
SEXUALLY BASED OFFENSES

00:04.072 --> 00:06.140
ARE CONSIDERED
ESPECIALLY HEINOUS.

00:06.174 --> 00:08.576
IN NEW YORK CITY,
THE DEDICATED DETECTIVES

00:08.609 --> 00:10.311
WHO INVESTIGATE
THESE VICIOUS FELONIES

00:10.344 --> 00:11.679
ARE MEMBERS
OF AN ELITE SQUAD

00:11.712 --> 00:13.314
KNOWN AS
THE SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT.

00:13.347 --> 00:15.549
THESE ARE THEIR STORIES.

00:17.118 --> 00:20.088
- GOOD ROLL, DANNY.
THAT'S MY PERFECT BOY.

00:20.121 --> 00:21.289
- GOOD JOB.

00:21.322 --> 00:22.823
- YOU'RE
A WONDERFUL TEACHER, ROGER.

00:22.856 --> 00:25.159
DANNY LOVES YOUR CLASSES.

00:25.193 --> 00:26.460
- THANKS, HANNAH,
GLAD TO HEAR IT.

00:26.494 --> 00:29.063
COME ON, SALLY.
TUCK YOUR HEAD.

00:29.097 --> 00:30.731
THAT'S IT.
GOOD JOB, GUYS.

00:30.764 --> 00:32.200
COME ON, KEEP IT GOING
HERE WE GO, HERE WE GO.

00:32.233 --> 00:33.834
- HANNAH DOESN'T GIVE
A DAMN ABOUT YOUR CLASS.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.337
WHAT SHE REALLY WANTS
IS TO RIP YOUR SWEATS OFF

00:36.370 --> 00:38.239
AND STRADDLE YOU LIKE
A POMMEL HORSE.

00:38.272 --> 00:40.374
- I DON'T THINK--
- DON'T GIVE ME ANY OF THAT

00:40.408 --> 00:42.710
"I NEVER SLEEP
WITH MY CLIENTS" CRAP.

00:42.743 --> 00:44.212
- I DON'T.

00:44.245 --> 00:46.114
- YOU SHOULD.

00:46.147 --> 00:48.182
- VERA, LOOK,
I'M FLATTERED.

00:48.216 --> 00:50.084
IT'S JUST...

00:50.118 --> 00:52.253
YOU'RE BARKING UP
THE WRONG TEE.

00:52.286 --> 00:54.155
- GOD.

00:54.188 --> 00:55.623
WOW, VERA, NICE GOING.

00:55.656 --> 00:58.726
- [baby crying]

00:58.759 --> 01:01.162
- OH, MY GOD.

01:01.195 --> 01:03.197
OH!

01:05.199 --> 01:07.701
YOU POOR BABY!
YOU MUST BE FREEZING.

01:07.735 --> 01:09.137
- [baby crying]

01:09.170 --> 01:12.140
- HELP!
SOMEONE CALL 9-1-1.

01:12.173 --> 01:13.207
[baby crying]

01:13.241 --> 01:16.210
- MALE INFANT, CAUCASIAN.

01:16.244 --> 01:18.112
CAME IN
SEVERELY HYPOTHERMIC.

01:18.146 --> 01:20.114
NO OBVIOUS SIGNS OF ABUSE.

01:20.148 --> 01:21.882
- LEFT OUT IN 30-DEGREE WEATHER?
THAT'S ABUSE.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.417
- OR ATTEMPTED MURDER.

01:23.451 --> 01:24.718
LITTLE GUY'S LUCKY
HE'S UNDER AN INCUBATOR

01:24.752 --> 01:25.719
AND NOT IN A COFFIN.

01:25.753 --> 01:26.854
- WHAT WAS HE WEARING
WHEN HE WAS BROUGHT IN?

01:26.887 --> 01:29.890
- JUST A ONESIE, WRAPPED
IN A COUPLE OF FLANNEL BLANKETS.

01:29.923 --> 01:31.192
WE SENT THEM
OVER TO YOUR CRIME LAB

01:31.225 --> 01:32.426
FOR EVIDENCE PROCESSING.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.195
- AND HE'S WHAT, DOC,
TWO MONTHS?

01:34.228 --> 01:36.464
- WELL, POSTERIOR FONTANELLE
IS ALMOST CLOSED,

01:36.497 --> 01:37.531
SO, YEAH,
THAT'S A GOOD ESTIMATE.

01:37.565 --> 01:40.268
- HOW LONG WILL HE NEED
TO STAY IN THIS INCUBATOR?

01:40.301 --> 01:41.335
- WE'RE WARMING
HIM UP SLOWLY.

01:41.369 --> 01:42.903
HIS CORE TEMP IS STILL LOW,

01:42.936 --> 01:44.705
SO HE'S NOT
OUT OF THE WOODS YET.

01:44.738 --> 01:47.675
- [sighs]

01:47.708 --> 01:49.510
WHY WOULD
SOMEONE DO THIS TO YOU?

02:03.957 --> 02:06.927
[suspenseful music]

02:06.960 --> 02:10.164
*

02:51.239 --> 02:52.473
- CANVASS OF THE NEIGHBORHOOD
TURNED UP NOTHING.

02:52.506 --> 02:54.208
NOBODY KNOWS ANYBODY
WITH A BOY THAT YOUNG.

02:54.242 --> 02:56.577
- MISSING PERSONS HASN'T HAD
A BABY REPORTED IN WEEKS.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.912
- SO EITHER MOMMY DOESN'T KNOW
THAT HER SON'S GONE...

02:58.946 --> 02:59.947
- OR SHE WAS THE ONE
WHO DUMPED HIM.

02:59.980 --> 03:01.649
- WELL, LAB'S
RUNNING HIS DNA.

03:01.682 --> 03:02.950
MAYBE WE'LL COME UP WITH
A FAMILIAL MATCH.

03:02.983 --> 03:04.918
THAT'S REALLY
ALL WE HAVE TO GO ON.

03:04.952 --> 03:05.986
- I'VE GOT
SOMETHING FOR YOU.

03:06.019 --> 03:07.455
YOU SEE THAT LOGO?

03:07.488 --> 03:09.290
THAT COMES FROM
A STORE CALLED BEBETIQUE,

03:09.323 --> 03:11.259
AN UPPER EAST SIDE
BABY STORE.

03:11.292 --> 03:12.460
- HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

03:12.493 --> 03:14.262
- MY NIECE REGISTERED THERE
FOR HER NEWBORN.

03:14.295 --> 03:17.465
A BLANKET I BOUGHT 'EM
COST ME TWO WEEKS OF OVERTIME.

03:17.498 --> 03:18.966
- WHAT WAS IT MADE OF, MINK?

03:18.999 --> 03:19.900
- ORGANIC COTTON.

03:19.933 --> 03:22.002
YOU JUST GOTTA CHECK OUT
THEIR PRICE TAGS.

03:22.035 --> 03:24.272
I'M TELLING YOU,
THAT BABY'S MOM'S GOT MONEY.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.807
- WHOA,
FIN WASN'T KIDDING.

03:26.840 --> 03:27.975
THESE PRICES
ARE OUTTA SIGHT.

03:28.008 --> 03:30.511
- LOT OF PARENTS WILL PAY
ANYTHING FOR PEACE OF MIND.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.312
- WELL, FOR FEW MORE BUCKS,

03:31.345 --> 03:32.680
THEY COULD
HIRE A SECURITY GUARD.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.682
- THIS PILLOW
IS EASIER ON YOUR BACK

03:34.715 --> 03:35.883
AND LITTLE INDIA RESTS

03:35.916 --> 03:37.685
MUCH MORE COMFORTABLY
WHILE SHE NURSES.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.287
- GREAT. THANK YOU.

03:39.320 --> 03:40.621
- HOW ARE YOU?
WE NEED HELP, TOO.

03:40.654 --> 03:42.490
- GETTING A HEAD START?
YOU'RE NOT EVEN SHOWING YET.

03:42.523 --> 03:44.592
- UH, PROFESSIONAL HELP.

03:44.625 --> 03:46.294
YOU SELL THAT?

03:46.327 --> 03:47.961
- IT'S ONE OF
OUR MOST POPULAR ITEMS.

03:47.995 --> 03:50.331
- WE ALSO HAVE A BABY
WHO NEARLY DIED LAST NIGHT.

03:50.364 --> 03:52.733
HE WAS WEARING
ONE OF YOUR ONESIES.

03:52.766 --> 03:53.901
- OH, MY GOD...

03:53.934 --> 03:56.870
- YOU SEEM TO KNOW THE NAMES
OF ALL YOUR CLIENTS' KIDS.

03:56.904 --> 03:58.872
YOU RECOGNIZE THIS BOY?

03:58.906 --> 04:00.708
- THAT'S JASPER,
DEDE ASTON'S BABY.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.376
- SHE SEEM BONDED
WITH JASPER?

04:02.410 --> 04:04.912
- COMPLETELY.
SHE ADORES HIM.

04:04.945 --> 04:06.347
IS JASPER OKAY?

04:06.380 --> 04:07.615
- YEAH, YEAH.

04:07.648 --> 04:09.049
BUT WE HAVE SOME QUESTIONS
FOR DEDE.

04:09.082 --> 04:10.584
DO YOU HAVE HER ADDRESS?
- WELL, LET ME CHECK.

04:10.618 --> 04:12.586
SHE'S IN OUR
FREQUENT BUYERS CLUB.

04:12.620 --> 04:13.987
- HAVE YOU EVER MET THE FATHER?

04:14.021 --> 04:15.889
- THERE ISN'T ONE.

04:15.923 --> 04:16.957
DEDE ADOPTED JASPER.

04:16.990 --> 04:19.860
SHE'S AN OLDER MOTHER--
WANTED TO START A FAMILY.

04:19.893 --> 04:22.996
[printer hums]

04:23.030 --> 04:25.032
HER CELL PHONE, EMAIL,
AND ADDRESS.

04:27.568 --> 04:30.904
[knocking]

04:30.938 --> 04:32.440
- DEDE'S NOT HOME.

04:32.473 --> 04:33.674
- OR ANSWERING HER PHONE.

04:33.707 --> 04:36.009
- THE BABY STORE OWNER SAID
DEDE SEEMED LIKE A GOOD MOTHER.

04:36.043 --> 04:37.978
I'M BEGINNING TO THINK
SOMEONE ELSE TOOK JASPER,

04:38.011 --> 04:39.613
AND MOM'S IN TROUBLE
AS WELL.

04:39.647 --> 04:41.415
- SOMEONE TOOK JASPER?

04:43.050 --> 04:43.951
- YOU DEDE'S NEIGHBOR?

04:43.984 --> 04:45.986
- WADE FISK.
I RENT HER GARDEN APARTMENT.

04:46.019 --> 04:48.622
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?
- WE'RE LOOKING FOR DEDE.

04:48.656 --> 04:51.058
- HAVEN'T SEEN HER
IN A FEW DAYS, BUT...

04:51.091 --> 04:53.427
OH, NO.
- WHAT?

04:53.461 --> 04:56.063
- LAST NIGHT I HEARD
YELLS COMING FROM HER PLACE.

04:56.096 --> 04:56.930
- YOU CALLED 911?

04:56.964 --> 05:00.401
- I THOUGHT IT WAS...
YOU KNOW...SEX.

05:00.434 --> 05:02.035
[muted cries, yells]
- YOU HEAR THAT?

05:02.069 --> 05:03.937
IT'S SPANISH,
PROBABLY NOT DEDE.

05:03.971 --> 05:06.073
- AYUDA ME, AYUDA ME!

05:06.106 --> 05:07.841
- THAT'S DEFINITELY
A CRY FOR HELP.

05:07.875 --> 05:09.543
- DOOR'S UNLOCKED.

05:09.577 --> 05:10.944
- [crying continues]

05:10.978 --> 05:12.913
AYUDA ME, AYUDA ME!
- POLICE.

05:12.946 --> 05:14.114
- POR FAVOR!
[crying]

05:14.147 --> 05:15.483
- MISS.
- [crying]

05:15.516 --> 05:17.685
- MISS, HEY.
I'M TALKING TO YOU.

05:17.718 --> 05:20.921
- THEY TOOK THE BABY!
- WHO TOOK THE BABY?

05:20.954 --> 05:23.824
- I DON'T KNOW.
BUT THE BABY'S GONE.

05:23.857 --> 05:25.092
- STAND UP.
WHO ARE YOU?

05:25.125 --> 05:27.395
- I'M IMELDA.
I'M JASPER'S NANNY.

05:27.428 --> 05:28.996
I TAKE CARE OF THE BABY.

05:29.029 --> 05:31.665
MISS DEDE'S OUT ON BUSINESS
IN BOSTON FOR TWO DAYS.

05:31.699 --> 05:33.767
AND I TAKE CARE OF THE BABY,
BUT HE'S GONE!

05:33.801 --> 05:34.902
- OKAY, IMELDA,
CALM DOWN.

05:34.935 --> 05:36.003
TELL US WHAT HAPPENED.

05:36.036 --> 05:36.937
- OKAY, I WENT
TO BED LAST NIGHT,

05:36.970 --> 05:39.072
AND EVERYTHING WAS FINE.
AND THIS MORNING,

05:39.106 --> 05:41.074
I CHECKED THE CRIB,
AND THE CRIB WAS EMPTY.

05:41.108 --> 05:42.776
AND I LOOKED HERE,
AND I LOOKED OUT ON THE STREET.

05:42.810 --> 05:44.578
BUT S-SOMEBODY STOLE HIM.

05:44.612 --> 05:46.013
- WHY DIDN'T
YOU CALL ANYBODY FOR HELP?

05:46.046 --> 05:47.448
- WHAT DO YOU THINK
I AM DOING?

05:47.481 --> 05:48.949
I'M PRAYING SOMEONE
WILL FIND JASPER.

05:48.982 --> 05:51.051
- YOUR PRAYERS
HAVE BEEN ANSWERED.

05:51.084 --> 05:54.455
WE FOUND THE BABY,
AND HE'S ALIVE.

05:54.488 --> 05:56.156
- GRACIAS POR DIO!
GRACIAS!

05:56.189 --> 05:58.892
- THE NEIGHBOR SAID HE HEARD
SCREAMING HERE LAST NIGHT.

05:58.926 --> 06:01.094
WHO WAS HERE
WITH YOU?

06:01.128 --> 06:03.063
- NO ONE. I WAS ALONE.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.398
- YOU SURE
ABOUT THAT, IMELDA?

06:04.432 --> 06:06.934
THERE'S A, UM...

06:06.967 --> 06:08.869
JUST FOUND A CONDOM
IN THE BATHROOM.

06:08.902 --> 06:11.038
- OH...
IT MUST BE FROM MISS DEDE.

06:11.071 --> 06:13.173
- YEAH, WELL,
SHE'S BEEN GONE FOR TWO DAYS,

06:13.206 --> 06:16.844
AND THIS LOOKS, UM...
KIND OF FRESH.

06:18.979 --> 06:20.147
- COME ON, IMELDA,
TELL THE TRUTH.

06:20.180 --> 06:23.984
- UH...OKAY, OKAY.

06:24.017 --> 06:25.786
MY BOYFRIEND WAS HERE.

06:25.819 --> 06:27.555
BUT HE WOULD
NEVER TAKE THE BABY.

06:27.588 --> 06:28.722
HE'S A RICH GUY.

06:28.756 --> 06:30.190
HE'S A HIGH-CLASS MAN,
AS YOU SAY.

06:30.223 --> 06:32.493
- GIVE ME A NAME.

06:32.526 --> 06:35.095
- HI, KEN TURNER.
YOU MUST BE DETECTIVE STABLER.

06:35.128 --> 06:38.065
- MR. TURNER, THANKS FOR
GETTING DOWN HERE SO QUICKLY.

06:38.098 --> 06:42.436
WHY DON'T WE GO SOMEWHERE
PRIVATE SO THAT WE CAN TALK.

06:42.470 --> 06:44.605
SAYS HERE
YOU USED TO BE AN A.D.A.

06:44.638 --> 06:45.706
- YEAH, NASSAU COUNTY.

06:45.739 --> 06:47.107
I WOULD'VE STUCK IT OUT,
BUT YOU KNOW,

06:47.140 --> 06:49.109
I COULDN'T MAKE ENDS MEET.
- MM-HMM.

06:49.142 --> 06:52.580
AND NOW YOU WORK FOR
DASCHLE PRIVATE EQUITY

06:52.613 --> 06:53.581
DOING CREDIT DEFAULT SWAPS?

06:53.614 --> 06:56.116
- YEAH, I KNOW.
GUYS LIKE ME TANKED THE ECONOMY.

06:56.149 --> 06:57.217
- SO IT IS TRUE.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.219
- WELL, IT'S A LITTLE
MORE COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

06:59.252 --> 07:00.320
- UH-HUH.
AS COMPLICATED AS

07:00.353 --> 07:02.956
A RICH, POWERFUL GUY
SCREWING SOME IMMIGRANT NANNY?

07:06.226 --> 07:07.495
- I DON'T FOLLOW.

07:07.528 --> 07:08.696
- IMELDA BARRIOS,

07:08.729 --> 07:10.798
LAST NIGHT AT
DEDE ASTON'S BROWNSTONE.

07:10.831 --> 07:12.065
ROUGH SEX,
IT SOUNDS LIKE.

07:12.099 --> 07:13.501
WE FOUND YOUR BROKEN RUBBER.

07:13.534 --> 07:14.968
- ROUGH SEX? NO.

07:15.002 --> 07:16.837
MAYBE A LITTLE...
ENTHUSIASTIC.

07:16.870 --> 07:19.206
BUT THAT'S NOT REALLY
A CRIME, NOW, IS IT, DETECTIVE?

07:19.239 --> 07:22.476
- NO, JUST
A LITTLE STRANGE.

07:22.510 --> 07:24.812
A WALL STREET MILLIONAIRE
IS SCREWING A NANNY

07:24.845 --> 07:26.814
WITH HER BOSS'S BABY
IN THE NEXT ROOM?

07:26.847 --> 07:29.617
I MEAN, HOW DOES DEDE ASTON
FEEL ABOUT THAT?

07:29.650 --> 07:32.085
- WELL, DEDE ASTON
DOESN'T KNOW ABOUT IT.

07:32.119 --> 07:33.053
I MEAN, WE'RE FRIENDS,

07:33.086 --> 07:34.588
BUT, YOU KNOW,
I DON'T TELL HER EVERYTHING.

07:34.622 --> 07:36.223
- LIKE YOU HITTING
ON HER HELP.

07:36.256 --> 07:39.259
- WELL, IMELDA'S BEAUTIFUL.
AND SO IS JASPER.

07:39.292 --> 07:40.961
HE'S A BEAUTIFUL BABY.
I LOVE BABIES.

07:40.994 --> 07:43.096
- ENOUGH TO STEAL ONE?

07:43.130 --> 07:45.065
- WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

07:45.098 --> 07:46.800
- SOMEONE GRABBED
JASPER LAST NIGHT.

07:46.834 --> 07:48.636
- IS HE OKAY?
- I WOULD WORRY ABOUT YOU

07:48.669 --> 07:50.871
BECAUSE WE FOUND
YOUR FINGERPRINTS ON HIS CRIB.

07:50.904 --> 07:53.674
- JUST TELL ME,
IS JASPER'S ALIVE?

07:53.707 --> 07:55.008
- BARELY. YEAH.

07:55.042 --> 07:56.777
BUT THE PROBLEM IS,
IMELDA SAID

07:56.810 --> 07:58.011
YOU WERE THE LAST PERSON
TO SEE HIM

07:58.045 --> 07:59.947
BEFORE HE WAS
LEFT TO DIE IN AN ALLEYWAY.

07:59.980 --> 08:01.982
- WELL, YEAH,
MY PRINTS ARE ON HIS CRIB

08:02.015 --> 08:03.216
BECAUSE I WENT TO
CHECK ON HIM.

08:03.250 --> 08:04.952
I CHECKED ON HIM
AROUND MIDNIGHT.

08:04.985 --> 08:07.087
HE WAS FINE.
AND I LEFT.

08:07.120 --> 08:10.123
YOU KNOW, I HAPPEN
TO BE FOND OF THAT BOY.

08:12.092 --> 08:13.961
- ARE YOU SUGGESTING
IMELDA IS NOT?

08:13.994 --> 08:15.596
- IMEL--

08:15.629 --> 08:19.533
LOOK, IMELDA IS BUILT FOR,
YOU KNOW, GREAT SEX.

08:19.567 --> 08:21.969
YOU KNOW, SHE'S
NOT REALLY NANNY MATERIAL.

08:22.002 --> 08:24.004
I MEAN, JASPER CRIES
NO MORE THAN MOST BABIES,

08:24.037 --> 08:25.005
BUT SHE CAN'T HANDLE IT.

08:25.038 --> 08:27.040
- SO YOU
THINK IMELDA SNAPPED?

08:29.743 --> 08:32.145
- I'M ONLY
SAYING IT WAS POSSIBLE.

08:35.282 --> 08:37.184
- SO, THINK
HE'S OUR BABY-NAPPER?

08:37.217 --> 08:38.218
- CAN'T RULE HIM OUT,

08:38.251 --> 08:40.554
BUT HE DEFINITELY
RULED IMELDA IN.

08:40.588 --> 08:43.023
SAID BABY JASPER'S
CRYING DRIVES HER CRAZY.

08:43.056 --> 08:44.958
- I'LL GO PICK HER UP.

08:44.992 --> 08:46.093
- [sighs]

08:46.126 --> 08:47.294
SO WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO ABOUT KEN?

08:49.997 --> 08:52.866
- WELL, LET HIM GO.

08:52.900 --> 08:56.103
FOR NOW.

08:56.136 --> 08:57.705
- DETECTIVE BENSON?

08:57.738 --> 08:59.807
- YES.
- I'M JASPER'S MOTHER.

08:59.840 --> 09:00.974
I GOT YOUR MESSAGES.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.610
I CAME STRAIGHT
FROM THE AIRPORT.

09:02.643 --> 09:04.111
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:04.144 --> 09:06.146
- MS. ASTON,
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE A SEAT?

09:07.681 --> 09:08.782
- SWEETHEART!

09:08.816 --> 09:10.918
- BABY,
THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

09:10.951 --> 09:12.986
- [sighs]
- SWEETHEART?

09:13.020 --> 09:15.756
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU TWO WERE JUST FRIENDS.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.760
- KEN'S MY FIANCE.

09:19.793 --> 09:21.328
- OH.

09:21.361 --> 09:23.631
TELL ME, WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:31.905 --> 09:34.041
- JASPER'S MY MIRACLE.

09:34.074 --> 09:35.843
WHEN CAN I TAKE HIM HOME?

09:35.876 --> 09:37.778
- AS SOON AS
HE'S MEDICALLY CLEARED

09:37.811 --> 09:40.814
AND WE CAN MAKE SURE
THAT HE'S SAFE.

09:43.416 --> 09:45.285
- WHY WOULDN'T
HE BE SAFE WITH ME?

09:45.318 --> 09:46.519
- WE KNOW THAT
YOU WERE OUT OF TOWN,

09:46.553 --> 09:49.289
BUT WE NEED TO RULE OUT EVERYONE
WHO HAS ACCESS TO YOUR HOME.

09:49.322 --> 09:51.391
- FINE.

09:51.424 --> 09:52.392
HOW CAN I HELP?

09:52.425 --> 09:53.861
- WELL, WHY DON'T
WE START AT THE BEGINNING?

09:53.894 --> 09:55.195
WHEN DID YOU ADOPT JASPER?

09:55.228 --> 09:56.329
- SEVEN WEEKS AGO.

09:56.363 --> 09:58.866
- AND HAVE YOU HAD ANY CONTACT
WITH THE BIRTH MOTHER?

09:58.899 --> 10:00.267
- NO, I DON'T
EVEN KNOW HER NAME.

10:00.300 --> 10:02.703
IT WAS A CLOSED ADOPTION.

10:02.736 --> 10:04.304
KEN DID THE LEGAL WORK.

10:04.337 --> 10:06.339
- YOUR FIANCE, KEN?
- YES.

10:06.373 --> 10:08.408
IT WAS A FRIEND OF
ONE OF HIS ASSOCIATES

10:08.441 --> 10:12.780
THAT KNEW THIS PREGNANT GIRL,
AND SHE COULDN'T KEEP HER BABY.

10:12.813 --> 10:14.648
KEN KNEW I WAS LOOKING.

10:14.682 --> 10:15.949
- AND YOU WERE ALREADY
ENGAGED AT THIS POINT?

10:15.983 --> 10:18.852
- NO. I BARELY KNEW KEN.

10:18.886 --> 10:22.389
IT WAS THIS ADOPTION
THAT SPARKED THINGS FOR US.

10:22.422 --> 10:24.324
[cell phone ringing]

10:24.357 --> 10:26.393
EXCUSE ME.

10:26.426 --> 10:28.929
I'M A MANAGEMENT CONSULTANT.

10:28.962 --> 10:32.065
AND MY WHOLE LIFE
HAS BEEN WORK, WORK, WORK.

10:32.099 --> 10:33.734
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T
EVEN HAVE TIME TO DATE.

10:33.767 --> 10:35.302
- I HEAR YOU.

10:35.335 --> 10:37.337
- WHEN I WASN'T GUNNING
FOR THE NEXT PROMOTION,

10:37.370 --> 10:39.840
I WAS OFF ON
